sql:
SELECT COUNT(call_id) AS total_calls
FROM customer_care
WHERE customer_rating > 3;

external_knowledge:
- 'shone the brightest in the realm of spending' refers to the top 3 customers with the highest total spending;
- 'personal details' include customer ID, name, email, phone number, gender, age, location, and registration date;
- 'loyalty status' refers to the customer's loyalty program status (active/inactive);
- 'rewards they are entitled to' are the rewards offered by the loyalty program in which they are enrolled.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT customer_id) AS number_of_loyal_customers
FROM customer_loyalty
WHERE points_earned > 50;

external_knowledge:
- "Product importance" is categorized as high, medium, or low, reflecting the perceived value of the product to the customer;
- "Customer satisfaction rating" is derived from the ratings given by customers during their care calls, averaged over all calls for each customer;
- "Loyalty program status" indicates whether a customer is active or inactive in the loyalty program, which can influence their overall satisfaction and engagement.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT c.name
FROM customers c
JOIN purchases p ON c.customer_id = p.customer_id;

external_knowledge:
- "stars in the product galaxy" refers to products with a high importance level;
- "shining brightly" emphasizes the high importance level of the products;
- "most frequently purchased" refers to the count of purchases.

- "Reliable" in this context refers to the shipping methods with the highest on-time delivery rates;
- "Percentage of deliveries that arrive on or before their expected date" is calculated as the average of the ratio of on-time deliveries to total shipments;
- "Top three" indicates the highest ranks based on the on-time delivery rate.

- Active loyalty customers are those whose `loyalty_program_status` is 'active';
- The `customer_id` is a unique identifier for each customer;
- The `purchase_amount` is the total amount spent by the customer in a single purchase;
- The `total_spent` is the sum of all `purchase_amount` for each customer.

- "Most loyal customers" refers to customers who have made more than one purchase;
- "Earned the most points" refers to the highest points in the loyalty program;
- "Recent purchases" refers to purchases made within the last six months.
